rooms.Name: Lag Square
rooms.Description:
You are now in Lag Square.  To the west is a forest and the towers of a
very large castle can be seen to the northwest.  The main part of town
is to the south and then east or west.

rooms.Name: A Small street
rooms.Description:
You have left town and are headed into the wilderness.  The houses are
fewer and the distance between them is greater.  The smog and busyness
of the city are slowly fading away.

rooms.Name: A Dark Path
rooms.Description:
You are traveling down a dark path through the forest.  You journey onward
in search of adventure, glory, levels, and money.

rooms.Name: A Dark Path
rooms.Description:
You are traveling down a dark path in the forest.  You have a little trouble
seeing where you are going, but continue on your journey.

rooms.Name: Entrance to the Lag forest
rooms.Description:
You have entered a small, bright forest.  The sunlight shines down on you
through the holes in the treeline.  The sounds of birds singing and small
animals scampering throught the forest can be heard.  In the distance
a large castle can be seen with many towers and brightly colored flags.

rooms.Name: The Lag Forest
rooms.Description:
You look at the beautiful trees surrounding you and can't help but feel at
peace with yourself . . . until you hear it.  NO, it can't be.  The echoes
of the dreaded word, "Ni!"   FEAR the word Ni!!!!!!!!

rooms.Name: A Knight guarding the gate
rooms.Description:
Here stands a large knight guarding a gate to a large wall to the north.
The wall seems to go on for miles in either direction so you decide to
approach the gate.   "HALT," the guard cries out!  "We are the knights who
say NI, in order for you to pass you must bring us a sacrafice . . . . . .
We demand a shrubbery!!"

rooms.Name: A Small Road
rooms.Description:
You are now on a small road headed toward the large castle that you have
been wondering about.  The road joins a much larger road comming from the
west up ahead.

rooms.Name: A Large Road
rooms.Description:
This large road heads directly into the castle gate.  The road going to
the west is blocked because of all of the flooding that happens during
this time of year.

rooms.Name: The Main Gate
rooms.Description:
You stand on a drawbrige looking up at a gigantic castle.  The castle has
a large cast iron gate and tall stone walls.  The castle is surrounded by
a moat and has thousands of brightly colored flags waving in the wind.  The
castle rests on a fairly large hill and is an impressive sight to behold.

rooms.Name: The Great Hall of Castle Lag
rooms.Description:
You have entered a Very large room.  The ceiling is covered with brightly
colored paintings depicting the history of The Land of Lag.  The gigantic
walls are covered with pictures of the royal family and many large mirrors.
People are constantly walking in and out of the room creating a lot of noise
and confusion.  The King and Queen are in their private room on the West side
of the castle, but remember to be polite or they might send you to the dungeon.

rooms.Name: The Main Stairway
rooms.Description:
You notice the red velvet carpet covering the marble staircase as you slowly
climb to the second floor.  There are two diamond lighting fixtures on either
side of the landing.  You marvel at the amount of money that must have been
spent to build this castle.

rooms.Name: The Reception
rooms.Description:
You are now in a small room off of the main hall.  This is where the royal
schedule is arranged.  The royal family is very busy and rarely has time to
talk to people.  Good luck getting an appointment!  As you look to your West
you see a giant red door.

rooms.Name: The Red Room
rooms.Description:
You have entered a long red room.  It has a large wooden dining table with
candles, several paintings of the her majesty, the Queen of Lag, and several
red chairs.  To the South is an enormous black door.

rooms.Name: The Black Room
rooms.Description:
This small room is entirely black in memory of the recent death of the
King's uncle.  A small picture of him rests on the table in the center
of the room.  You begin to get a cold, mysterious feeling and decide
that it would be good to get out of this room.  A giant golden door
stands before you.

rooms.Name: The Room of gold
rooms.Description:
WOW! Gold in every direction!!!!!!!  This is where the king keeps his
his spending money.  In the corner is, yet another, picture of the royal
family.  To the south is a huge white door.

rooms.Name: The Room of White
rooms.Description:
You are blinded by the light reflecting off of the walls.  After your eyes
have adjusted you realize that you are in the royal reception.  Before you
sits the King and Queen of Lag.  You bow humbly and approach them.

rooms.Name: A Dark Hallway
rooms.Description:
You are traveling down a dark hallway.  It appears to be part of an older
section of the castle.  There is also an unpleasant musty smell comming from
ahead.

rooms.Name: Down into the Dungeon
rooms.Description:
You must travel down a flight of stone stairs into the Dungion of Castle Lag.
The sounds of misery and dispear can be heard from below.  In addition, the
faint glow of torches can be seen ahead.

rooms.Name: A Cell
rooms.Description:
The sight of this smelly room with no light or window is enough to make
anyone obey the law.  The stench is almost unbearable and you pity the
poor soul that has to live in this filthy mess.  If they are still alive
they must be tough.

rooms.Name: The Dungeon Hallway
rooms.Description:
You notice that the hallway is lit by numerous glowing torches which line the
walls.  On either side of you is a dungeon cell where some type of offender is
being held.  At the end of the hall you notice an open door on the West and
a passage to the East.

rooms.Name: The office of the Dungeon Keeper
rooms.Description:
You enter a small office with dirt and grime everywhere.  It looks as if it
has never been cleaned.  There is a small desk behind which is sitting the
powerful Keeper of the Dungeon.  In the corner you see large barrels used
for storing the Lag Dragon's food.  The Keeper smiles at you as you enter
because feeding the dragon is a lot of work you'll be saving him.

a passage to the East.

rooms.Name: A Dark Hallway
rooms.Description:
This hallway is in even worse condition than the previous one.  The Ceiling
looks like it could give way at any moment . . . The walls are covered with
all sorts of insects and worms.  From ahead you hear the sounds of death, 
fire, and almost certain destruction.

rooms.Name: The Dragon's Lair
rooms.Description:
This is the home of the most powerful creature in all of the land.  FEAR the
Lag Dragon!  The Lair is well lit and as you enter you hear cheering.  When
you look up you see hundreds of spectators watching you from above.  The 
King and Queen are even in attendance.  Good Luck!

Lag Dragon!  The Lair is well lit and as you enter you hear cheering.  When
you look up you see hundreds of spectators watching you from above.  The 
King and Queen are even in attendance.  Good Luck!

rooms.Name: The Dragon's Lair
rooms.Description:
This is the home of the most powerful creature in all of the land.  FEAR the
Lag Dragon!  The Lair is well lit and as you enter you hear cheering.  When
you look up you see hundreds of spectators watching you from above.  The 
King and Queen are even in attendance.  Good Luck!

rooms.Name: The Prince's Room
rooms.Description:
The first impression that you get from the room is that it would be every
child's dream.  The walls are a bright blue color with clowns and animals
painted on them.  Toys and books are scattered throught the room.  The large
bed in the center of the room is almost completely covered with blocks and
other toys.

rooms.Name: The Court Magician's Room
rooms.Description:
As you enter you feel as if you have been swept into a land of ancient
mystery.  Hundereds of old books line the walls collecting dust.  You walk
up to one that is lying open on the floor and looks as if it is in another
language.  As you look over at the Magician you can see lightning strike
outside the window directly behind him.  This gives you an uneasy feeling.

rooms.Name: The Northwest corner
rooms.Description:
You have come to a small corner hallway connecting several rooms.  This is the
corner of the building that the young Prince of Lag roams in search of
someone to bother.  Due to the granting of every whim and desire that the
Prince has he has become a rather spoiled brat.  His favorite activity is
to drive the servents, especially his Nanny, crazy.

rooms.Name: The Nanny's room
rooms.Description:
This must be the most organized room that you have ever entered.  The bed is
neatly made and could pass even the strictest military inspection.  The
Nanny's clothes are arranged by day worn and are neatly hanging in her open
closet.  No trace of dust can be found anywhere in her room, which is quite
a feat considering the mess that the Prince makes.

rooms.Name: The Northeast corner
rooms.Description:
This small hallway connects several rooms with the Main Stairway of Castle
Lag.  To the south is the King's meeting hall where important decisions
regarding the kingdom are made.  You hear people talking and decide that
they probably won't mind if you take a look in.  To the West you hear all
sorts of noise.

rooms.Name: The Toy Room
rooms.Description:
You enter a room with thousands of toys piled up throught the room.  You
are amazed at the number of them; how could he possibly have the time!!!
The room is a bright yellow color with large windows on the west wall.  To
the south is the King's private study.

rooms.Name: The Meeting Room
rooms.Description:
Several important figures sit in this room discussing the affairs of state.
The King, due to his busy schedule is absent today.  The ministers of various
departments are talking about the kingdom in their elegant gold chairs.

rooms.Name: The King's Private Study
rooms.Description:
This long room is where the king spends time relaxing and reading.  The walls s
are lined with thousands of books on just about everything.  The room is well
furnished with a large wooden desk and several fancy wooden chairs.  This is
where the king hides from the everyday commotion that keeps him busy.

rooms.Name: The Queen's Reading Room
rooms.Description:
The light colors and beautiful smell indicate that you must be in the
room of a lady.  This is where the queen goes to read her favorite books
about knights and romance.  A stack of books sits on a small table next to
the fireplace.  To the north is the meeting room and the south is the
southwest corner of the castle.

rooms.Name: The Southwest corner
rooms.Description:
This hallway connects the King's study with the room of the captain of the
guard.  It is a small, but well decorated hallway with two small windows
overlooking the surrounding countryside.

rooms.Name: The Office of the Captain of the Guard
rooms.Description:
The room that you have entered is oval in shape with a slightly domed
ceiling.  A beautiful red tapestry hangs on the north wall and crossed
swords hang above the doorways.  The corner hallways are to the east and
west.

rooms.Name: The Southeast Corner
rooms.Description:
This corner of the castle connects the queen's reading room with the
Captain of the Guard's room and the Southeast tower.  From the small
windows you can get a good view of The Land of Lag and beyond.

rooms.Name: The Southwest Tower
rooms.Description:
The southern towers serve as look out posts because they are much taller
than the northern towers.  From here you can see anywhere in the kingdom
and beyond!

rooms.Name: The Hut of a Shrubber
rooms.Description:
You have entered a small hut on the northern edge of town.  It has a straw
thatched roof and thin log walls.  It is dimly lit by the fire glowing in
the northeast corner of the hut.  Brian the shrubber sits on his old stool
arranging a shrubbery for sale.
